command:example.dev:code:
PS C:\> $Name = "HP ProLiant BL460 Gen9 Profile Template"
PS C:\> $con1 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net 41-A" -ApplianceConnection MyAppliance1.domain.com | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 1
PS C:\> $con2 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net 41-B" -ApplianceConnection MyAppliance1.domain.com | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 2
PS C:\> $bl460SHT = Get-HPOVServerHardwareTypes -name "BL460c Gen9 1"
PS C:\> $eg = Get-HPOVEnclosureGroup "Default EG1"
PS C:\> $params = @{
>>    name                = $Name;
>>    serverHardwareType  = $bl460SHT;
>>    enclosureGroup      = $eg;
>>    connections         = $con1, $con2;
>>    ApplianceConnection = 'MyAppliance1.domain.com'
>>}
>>
PS C:\> New-HPOVServerProfileTemplate @params | Wait-HPOVTaskComplete

PS C:\> $profileName = 'SQL DB Cluster Node Template v1.0'
PS C:\> $bl660SHT = Get-HPOVServerHardwareTypes -name "BL660c Gen9 1"
PS C:\> #display the BL660 Gen9 BIOS Settings
PS C:\> $bl660SHT.biosSettings
PS C:\> #Set HP Power Profile (ID 210) to Maximum Performance and HP Power Regulator (ID 140) to HP Static High Performance Mode.
PS C:\> $bl660bios = @(@{id=210;value=3},@{id=140;value=3})
PS C:\> $enclosuregroup = Get-HPOVEnclosureGroup "Production EG1"
PS C:\> $con1 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net 41-A" | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 1
PS C:\> $con2 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net 41-B" | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 2
PS C:\> $con3 = Get-HPOVNetwork "fabric a" -ApplianceConnection MyAppliance1.domain.com | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -id 3 -type FibreChannel -bootable -priority Primary -arrayWWPn "21:11:00:02:AC:00:72:03" -LUN 0
PS C:\> $con4 = Get-HPOVNetwork "fabric b" -ApplianceConnection MyAppliance1.domain.com | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -id 4 -type FibreChannel -bootable -priority Secondary -arrayWWPn "22:12:00:02:AC:00:72:03" -LUN 0
PS C:\> $LogicalDisk = New-HPOVServerProfileLogicalDisk -Name 'My Local Disk' -RAID RAID1 -NumberofDrives 2 -DiskType SasSsd 
PS C:\> $volume1 = Get-HPOVStorageVolume SharedVolume1 -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com' | New-HPOVServerProfileAttachVolume
PS C:\> $params = @{
>>    name                = $profileName;
>>    assignmentType      = "server"
>>    server              = $server;
>>    connections         = $con1, $con2, $con3, $con4;
>>    bios                = $true;
>>    biossettings        = $bl660bios
>>    manageboot          = $True;
>>    bootMode            = "UEFI";
>>    pxeBootPolicy       = "IPv4ThenIPv6";
>>    bootOrder           = "HardDisk";
>>    HideUnusedFlexnics  = $True;
>>    LocalStorage        = $True;
>>    Initialize          = $True;
>>    LogicalDisk         = $LogicalDisk;
>>    SANStorage          = $True;
>>    Ostype              = 'Win2k12';
>>    StorageVolume       = $volume1;
>>    ApplianceConnection = 'MyAppliance.domain.com'
>> }
>>    
PS C:\> New-HPOVServerProfileTemplate @params | Wait-HPOVTaskComplete

maml:description.maml:para:
Single object returned from appliance. If Async task, a Hashtable is returned with the following contents:

     @{
         uri = TaskUri;
         category = "tasks";
         type = "TaskResourceV2";
         taskState = "New";
         resource = @{};
     }

If no resources are found, a PsCustomObject is returned that contains:

 	@{
 		statusCode = [int]HTTP Status Code;
 		statusMessage = [string]HTTP Status Message;
 		lastCall = [string]URI;
 	}
